Before processing a claim for cash advance, the Municipal Accountant shall ensure that the previous cash advance of the concerned official or employee has been settled;

The Municipal Accountant shall strictly monitor that all cash advances granted are liquidated within the required period of settlement;

Submit a copy of the demand letter issued to the ICO-Municipal Treasurer together with pertinent documents to prove its settlement, if any; and

Require the ICO-Municipal Treasurer to immediately settle all unliquidated cash advances. She shall maintain a record of all cash advances received and liquidated to serve as a ready reference in determining the unliquidated balance per cash advance received so as to prevent the accumulation of long outstanding cash advances.

We reiterated our recommendation that Management:

Present regular/ flagship programs/projects of the LGU under the section, Attributed Programs of the GAD Plan and Budget and the GAD Accomplishment Report;

Employ the HGDG tool for regular/flagship programs/projects of the LGU and identify which part of the project cost/expenditure is attributable to the GAD Budget;

Maximize the utilization of the GAD funds through the identification and implementation of GAD-related programs and projects in order to attain the objectives for which funds were provided; 

Strictly observe the timelines in the submission of GPB and GAD AR to the Audit Team; and

Capacitate the GFPS by allowing them to attend trainings and seminars especially on the use of the HGDG tool.

