observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:
 Created Inventory Committee (a) prepare a concrete plan for the conduct of a complete physical inventory including the time frame to complete inventory count and (b) use the summary of PPE per offices in the conduct of actual physical inventory;
 MGSO-Designate obtain from the Accounting Office the list of properties per category of PPE as reference in the inventory taking and preparation of report;
 Municipal Accountant and MGSO-Designate coordinate and prepare supporting schedules to facilitate the proper reconciliation of the property accounts and establishment of actual existence, ownership and condition of the properties; and the
 Municipal Accountant maintain Property Ledgers for the complete breakdown of the amounts reflected in the Financial Statements, effect proper adjustments in the books for items that necessitate corrections as identified in the verification and reconciliation process, create separate Subsidiary Ledgers for the unreconciled account balances and observe proper disclosure of the same in the Notes to Financial Statements for fair presentation.

We recommended that:
the Municipal Mayor create and establish an Inventory Committee, headed by the MGSO with representatives from the Accounting and Assessor’s Office, which will: 
Conduct complete physical inventory of all recorded Municipal properties within a time frame set by the Municipal Mayor;

Prepare RPCPPE for the results of the inventory taking; and
•	Prepare IIRUP for determined unserviceable properties supported with proper documentation for the subsequent disposal of the same in accordance with COA rules and regulations;
the MGSO and MAccO prepare Property Cards simultaneous to the inventory taking to facilitate preparation of RPCPPE and reconciliation of records between Property and Accounting Offices. The same should be maintained by both offices to facilitate the recording of acquisition and disposal of the properties;

the MGSO and MAccO conduct periodic reconciliation of property records; and


the Municipal Accountant maintain Property Ledgers Cards for each classification of PPE account, make pertinent entries for determined adjustments/errors upon conduct of physical count, and observe proper disclosures in the Notes to Financial Statement to address matters regarding existence and ownership of the recorded properties.
